<p><span style="font-family: Baskerville Old Face;"><span style="font-size:250%;">IRL Commentary</span></span></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/a-circus-milked-dry">A Circus Milked Dry</a></li>
<li><a href="/a-circus-of-a-wreck">A Circus of a Wreck</a></li>
<li><a href="/a-circus-with-paranoia">A Circus With Paranoia</a></li>
</ul>
<p>All of my Circus Clowns Tales were fun to write, mainly because there are so many things you can do with shape-shifting Eldritch Clowns. A big key point in these Tales came from <a href="/scp-1921">SCP-1921</a>. CLOWN MILK.</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/free-freaks">Free Freaks</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Another Circus Tale involving people of the freak show. I'll eventually write a sequel, but honestly having a bit of writer's block on how to proceed.</p>
